g that the JSON is valid without adding any Markdown. I want to be precise!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"doxia-site-renderer 2.0.0 is a Plexus/Sisu component whose meaningful rendering paths need container injection, a provided Maven Artifact API for public skin-related methods, and an explicit Doxia parser module for common APT site documents because parser modules are no longer supplied by doxia-core.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The 2.0.0 public API exposes org.apache.maven.artifact.Artifact in SiteRenderingContext, SiteRenderer, and DefaultSiteRenderer skin methods, but the artifact declares maven-artifact as provided so it is not pulled in by the normal test scaffold.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-testing:1.4.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"DefaultSiteRenderer relies on injected Plexus/Sisu services such as VelocityComponent, ParserModuleManager, Doxia, and PlexusContainer; upstream tests use plexus-testing to obtain an injected SiteRenderer instead of directly constructing DefaultSiteRenderer.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"APT is a normal Maven site source format and the 2.0.0 POM notes that Doxia parser modules are no longer in doxia-core and must be stated explicitly so their component descriptors are discovered.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment variable is indicated. Rewrite tests for the 2.0.0 API: use DocumentRenderingContext instead of the removed RenderingContext class, do not call enableLogging, and do not use the removed SkinResourceLoader. For renderer behavior, obtain SiteRenderer through a Plexus/Sisu test container and initialize SiteRenderingContext with a SiteModel plus input/output encodings; skin-resource tests should create a small skin JAR and an Artifact if exercising createContextForSkin or copyResources.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Existing 1.9.1 tests are API-incompatible with 2.0.0, so extra setup alone will not fix compilation.\",\n    \"If generated tests cover XDOC or FML documents rather than APT, the corresponding doxia-module-xdoc or doxia-module-fml test dependency may also be needed.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_011dd25493fe6d12016a3f2a892b748194b0717ea6b8b5299e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2217, "output": 860, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39941, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782524546319, "responseId": "resp_011dd25493fe6d12016a3f2a82e61881948ff3342379e1befe"}}
